Hi, I'm Rene Schallner.

I build things — software, tools, products — at the intersection of AI and research. Currently running [AI Research & Technology Lab](https://technologylab.ai) in Vienna, where I'm building [QualCode](https://qualcode.ai) and [LaBrowser](https://labrowser.technologylab.ai).

Before that: Chief Founding Engineer at [ZML](https://zml.ai), 8 years at [NIM](https://nim.org) (Nuremberg Institute for Market Decisions), medical tech, telecom. I've been writing code for a long time and I still find it genuinely interesting.

># [Open Source]($block.attrs('warning'))
>- **⚡ZAP⚡:** [blazingly fast backends in zig](https://zigzap.org)
>- **Telekasten.nvim:** [Note-taking / Zettelkasten in Neovim](https://github.com/nvim-telekasten/telekasten.nvim)
>- More on the [projects page](/projects)

I [write here](/blog) about what I'm building, thinking about, and occasionally getting wrong.

Feel free to reach out on [X](https://twitter.com/renerocksai) or [LinkedIn](https://linkedin.com/in/rene-schallner), or browse [GitHub](https://github.com/renerocksai).
